Privacy Policy

Last updated: 18.02.2025

Bettors ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application Bettors (the "App").

1. Information We Collect

We do not collect personally identifiable information. However, we may collect non-personal data for analytics and app improvement purposes, including:
- Device information (e.g., model, operating system version)
- Usage data (e.g., interactions with the App, time spent in the App)
- IP address (anonymized for security and analytics)

2. How We Use Your Information

We use collected data to:
- Improve user experience and App functionality
- Analyze usage trends and enhance performance
- Ensure compliance with security and legal requirements

3. Data Sharing and Third Parties

We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information. However, we may share anonymized data with third-party services for analytics, such as:
- Google Analytics for Firebase (for app usage insights)
- Crashlytics (for error tracking and debugging)

4. Data Security

We implement appropriate security measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

5. Your Rights and Choices

Since we do not collect personal information, users do not need to request data deletion. However, you can disable data collection for analytics through your device settings.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify users of significant changes through the App or other means.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: danielyan@bettorsapp.com

By using the Bettors App, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.

